criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
- Postpartum women (early months postpartum) aged 18+ with OUD maintained on BT who are 1) able to read, hear and understand English adequately enough to provide informed consent and fully comprehend all study requirements and 2) having birthed a medically healthy infant > 34 weeks' gestation, without major malformation or developmental delay, and 3) willing to engage in MP or enhanced usual care at OUD clinics
Exclusion Criteria:
- 1) require immediate clinical care for suicidal or homicidal risk (please see Protection of Human Subjects section for clinical management of suicidal risk);
- 2) meet DSM-5 criteria forfor bipolar or a psychotic disorder;
- 3) have medical conditions requiring medication including HIV; hepatitis; kidney disease; chronic hypertension; heart disease; coronary artery disease; autoimmune disorders including lupus, Type 1 or Type 2 diabetes or gestational diabetes on insulin; asthma requiring steroid inhaler.
